    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://chicago.craigslist.org/wcl/fbh/6040695255.html"></div>
        </div>
<b>Michael Jordan's Restaurant  - OPENING SOON in Oakbrook! </b><br>
<br>
The <b>General Manager</b> plays an integral role in providing polished, personalized service to the guests of our Chicago location, on Michigan Avenue.<br>
<br>
<b>**Fine dining experience and in-depth knowledge of food and wine are a MUST. </b><br>
<i>Candidates without these qualifications will not be considered. </i><br>
<br>
<b>General responsibilities include: </b><br>
&#9726;Supervising, monitoring and participating in service operations during an assigned shift <br>
&#9726;Regularly interacting with guests to ensure quality dining experiences <br>
&#9726;Opening and/or closing the restaurant <br>
&#9726;Implementing new-hire and on-going training for host &amp; service staff <br>
&#9726;Interviewing and hiring of host staff <br>
&#9726;Managing staff and/or restaurant manager performance through effective use of informal and formal feedback, recognition, coaching &amp; counseling meetings, disciplinary action, annual evaluations, etc.; assists in developing restaurant managers to ensure readiness for growth/promotion <br>
&#9726;Implements marketing and promotion strategies as directed <br>
&#9726;Performing various administrative functions including: conducting pre-shifts, processing server checkouts, preparing schedules, conducting inventory, placing orders, etc.<br>
<br>
<b>QUALIFICATIONS </b><br>
Requirements include 3-5 years prior management experience in an upscale, fine dining setting. Candidates with strong service backgrounds but with more limited management experience will be considered and are encouraged to apply. Must have strong food and beverage/wine knowledge. Prior steak house experience preferred. Ideal candidates will also demonstrate: <br>
&#9726;the ability to foster genuine relationships with guests <br>
&#9726;an upbeat, "hands-on," accountable, results-driven, and pro-active mindset <br>
&#9726;exceptional people skills and the ability to motivate others to do their best <br>
&#9726;outstanding communication and organizational skills <br>
&#9726;strong computer skills<br>
<br>
In return, we offer a competitive financial and benefits package including medical/dental/vision insurance, disability and life insurance, matching 401k plan, collaborative work environment where your contributions count!<br>
<br>
<b><i>Interested? </b></i>We'd like to talk to you if you have the experience required and passion for providing a superb guest experience. Submit your resume, cover letter &amp; salary history to this posting.<br>    </section>

<ul class="notices">
            <li>Principals only. Recruiters, please don't contact this job poster.</li>
            <li>do NOT contact us with unsolicited services or offers</li>
</ul>

